apt-get command is used to install software
apt means advanced packaging tool. It is available for debian based operating system, nor Redhat based. For Redhat, it is yum.


fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ sudo apt-get update     ;Updating the whole package

fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ nano /etc/apt/sources.list      ;Shows all the packages

fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ vlc -version        ;Trying to see if vlc is installed. vlc is not installed

Command 'vlc' not found, but can be installed with:

sudo snap install vlc      # version 3.0.7, or
sudo apt  install vlc-bin

See 'snap info vlc' for additional versions.

fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ sudo apt-get install        ;Installing vlc

fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ sudo apt-get remove vlc     ;Just removing the vlc software

fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ sudo apt-get remove --purge vlc     ;Removing configuration files of vlc

fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ sudo apt-get autoremove vlc         ;Some packages were automatically installed while installing vlc. We no longer need them.


